## Constraints

- Library error types MUST use typed enums (thiserror), not Box<dyn Error>.
- Every error variant MUST carry context data, not just a name.
- Error messages MUST be actionable — tell the user what to do.
- Source errors MUST be chained with `#[source]`, not stringified.
- Never discard errors silently. If ignoring is intentional, use `let _ =`.
- Never use `.unwrap()` or `.expect()` in library code.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully.

